{{Infobox language |name=Payaguá |nativename= |states=[[Argentina]], [[Paraguay]] |ethnicity=[[Payaguá people]] |extinct=ca. 1900 |ref=<ref>[http://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/00141844.1949.9980693#.UZuuCEBDuG9 The Payaguá Indians], written in 1949, notes the tribe has been extinct for ~50 years.</ref> |familycolor=American |fam1=[[Guaicuruan languages|Guaicuruan]]? |fam2=Eastern |iso3=none |linglist=qho |glotto=paya1236 |glottorefname=Payagua }}
'''Payaguá''' (Payawá) is an extinct language of [[Paraguay]], [[Argentina]], and [[Bolivia]], spoken by the [[Payaguá people|Payaguá Indians]]. It is usually classified as one of the [[Guaicuruan languages]], but the data is insufficient to demonstrate that.<ref name=Glottolog/>
